<section id="examtips">
	<p class="popuptext">In Set 1 we saw how static charts do not show changes over time. If you are asked to write a report on a static chart, you will not have to describe trends, but you are expected to make comparisons between values.</p>
	
	<p class="popuptext">Here are some ways of making comparisons.</p>
	
	<p class="popuptext"><span color="#0000FF">More films were produced in the Czech Republic than in Bulgaria.</span></p>
	
	<p class="popuptext"><span color="#0000FF">The number of films produced in the Czech Republic was double the number of films produced in Bulgaria.</span></p>
	
	<p class="popuptext"><span color="#0000FF">Twice as many films were produced in the Czech Republic as in Bulgaria.</span></p>
	
	<p class="popuptext"><span color="#0000FF">The number of films produced in the Czech Republic was twice as many as the number produced in Bulgaria.</span></p>
	
	<p class="popuptext"><span color="#0000FF">The number of films produced in the Czech Republic was twice as high as the number produced in Bulgaria.</span></p>
	
</section>
